 divisional managers' decisions with the organization's primary objective of maximizing shareholders' wealth.", "\"ADVANTAGES OF ROI\":\"Advantages of ROI include ease of comparison between divisions, focus on scarce capital resources, encouragement of reduction in non-essential investment, and easily understood percentages.\"", "\"DISADVANTAGES OF ROI\":\"Disadvantages of ROI include the risk of dysfunctional decision-making, subjective definition of capital employed, potential increase in ROI over time due to depreciation, and risk of window-dressing.\"", "\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\":Residual Income (RI) is the amount of income that an individual or company has after all expenses have been paid. It is calculated by subtracting the imputed interest charge from the net profit. RI serves as a measure of the profitability of an investment after accounting for the cost of capital. Specifically, it is determined by taking the divisional profit and deducting the imputed interest charge. For instance, Division A has a Residual Income of $2.552 million, while Division B has a Residual Income of $2.322 million. This metric focuses on wealth creation by deducting an imputed interest expense from the pre-tax profit.", "\"IMPUTED INTEREST\":\"Imputed interest\" is a notional interest charge calculated on the capital employed by the head office. It is determined by multiplying the capital employed by the interest rate. This imputed interest is used in the calculation of residual income.", "\"QUIZ: ROI AND RESIDUAL INCOME\":\"This quiz involves calculating the current ROI and residual income for Division X and showing how they would change under two proposals.\"", "\"ROI\":Return on Investment (ROI) is a performance measure used to evaluate the efficiency or profitability of an investment or to compare the efficiency of several different investments. It is calculated by dividing the net profit by the cost of the investment and is expressed as a percentage. Specifically, ROI can be calculated using the formula: (Net Profit / Operating Net Assets) * 100, or alternatively, Profit / Opening Investment (Net Book Value). This measure helps in assessing the profitability of an investment or division by comparing net profit to the capital employed.", "\"RI\":\"RI (Residual Income) is calculated as the net operating income minus the product of the investment cost and the cost of capital. It is used to measure the absolute amount of profit generated above the required return.\"", "\"PROPOSAL 1\":\"Proposal 1 offers a 15% return ($0.15m/$1m), which is greater than the cost of capital. However, it leads to a decrease in divisional ROI, which could result in the divisional manager rejecting it. Residual income increases if Proposal 1 is adopted, leading to goal-congruent decisions.\"", "\"PROPOSAL 2\":\"Proposal 2 is not acceptable to the company. The return on existing assets is 13% ($0.3m/$2.3m), which is greater than the cost of capital and hence should not be disposed of. However, divisional ROI rises, which could lead to the divisional manager accepting it. Residual income decreases if Proposal 2 is adopted, leading to goal-congruent decisions.\"", "\"QUIZ: RESIDUAL INCOME\":\"This quiz involves evaluating the performance of divisional managers using residual income. It includes scenarios where managers must decide on investment projects based on residual income calculations.\"", "\"ADVANTAGES OF RESIDUAL INCOME\":\"Residual income overcomes some of the problems associated with ROI, such as dysfunctional behavior and holding on to old assets. It can be linked to net present value, reflecting the best way to make investment decisions. A risk-adjusted cost of capital can reflect different risk positions of different divisions.\"", "\"DISADVANTAGES OF RESIDUAL INCOME\":\"Residual income has several disadvantages, including the definition of capital employed, the effect of depreciation, window dressing, and the challenge of comparing divisions of different sizes. It is also less easily understood than a percentage.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}